Etymology. The species name (
guadeloupae
) is a feminine genitive singular noun, referring to the distribution of the species on Guadeloupe . In the past, the name " Guadeloupe " was used synonymously with Basse-Terre, where the type material was probably collected and the island where the species is thought to be endemic.
